<div class="game-rules-container">
    <h3>Overview</h3>
    <p>Coup is a game of bluffing and deduction set in a dystopian universe. Players represent powerful members of society who are secretly vying for influence over the government.</p>

    <h3>Gameplay</h3>
    <p>The game is played in turns, with each player taking one action per turn. The available actions are:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Income: Take one coin from the Treasury.</li>
        <li>Foreign Aid: Take two coins from the Treasury. (Can be blocked by a player claiming to have a Duke)</li>
        <li>Tax: Take three coins from the Treasury. (Can be blocked by a player claiming to have a Duke)</li>
        <li>Exchange: Exchange your Influence cards with two cards from the Court deck.</li>
        <li>Assassinate: Pay three coins to launch an assassination attempt against another player's Influence card. (Can be blocked by a player claiming to have a Contessa)</li>
        <li>Steal: Steal two coins from another player. (Can be blocked by a player claiming to have a Captain or Ambassador)</li>
        <li>Coup: Pay seven coins to launch a coup against another player, forcing them to lose one Influence card.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Winning the Game</h3>
    <p>The last player with Influence cards remaining wins the game.</p>

</div>